The healthcare industry is one of the worlds largest and fastest-growing industries. Consuming over 10 percent of gross domestic product (GDP) of most developed nations, health care can form an enormous part of a countrys economy. Home health care Medicare-certified services may include short-term nursing, rehabilitative, therapeutic, and assistive home health care. Home health agencies provide services to beneficiaries who are homebound and need skilled nursing or therapy. In 2011, about 3.4 million Medicare beneficiaries received home care, and the program spent about $18.4 billion on home health services. The number of agencies participating in Medicare reached 12,199 in 2012.

On this paper we will use 2011 data from medicare.gov and take a closer look at Norther Virginia Home Health Care providers. The objective of the exploration is to see if there is a correlation with patient rating of agency and the medicare revenue. The paper will explores patient sentiment towards the providers, star ratings, types of providers and the top and list grossing providers in the the state. There were 249 home health care agencies registered with medicare. The total revenue paid by medicare to the agencies state wide was $445,825,098.00. (four hundred forty six million US dollars)

The questions this paper attempt to answer are the following:

Did HHC agencys high positive patient rating resulted in higher revenue?
_Which home health care provider in Virginia had the highest/lowest patient recommendation?__
On average which type of ownership HHC generated the highest revenue?

Question that can be answered to increase service and marketshare but are not included here are the following.
* How does HHC abc" rating/revenue compare to its local county, State wide and the entire US competitors?
* What are the important metrics for HHC agency abc to improve increase patient rating?
* Which hospital refers the most HHC customers to agencys?
* What is the seasonal pattern for the number of patients available? * What is the profile of the top 10 types of customers (age, sickness type, average amount billed)?
 * Can we predict the customers who are likely to go back to the hospital? * For marketing what is the demographic in my local and neighboring county?

Take Aways:

  1. HHC agencies who had a higher patient recommendation generally show higher revenue and the once with lower patient rating earned less. But there were few exceptions. For example, the highest 4 revenue earners had their patient rating ranging only between 75% and 82%.
  2. With 98% patient recommendation and 5 out of 5 star rating Helping hands home health care, Inc ranked at the very top, while Professional health care resources, Inc was at the bottom with 53% patient recommendation and 2 out of 5 starting.
  3. With the average earning of $4.7 million the Visiting Nurse association agencies earned the highest. Followed by Hospital based programs with the average of $2.8 Million. Official health Agencies had the lowest revenue with average earnings of $680 thousand.

Professionals providing home care include

  • licensed practical nurses,
  • registered nurses,
  • home health aides,
  • physical therapists,
  • occupational therapists and
  • social workers.

Rehabilitation services may be provided by

  • physical therapists,
  • occupational therapists,
  • speech and
  • language pathologists and
  • dietitian

Who pays

  • Medicare/Medicaid
  • private insurance, or
  • self/family
  • Private insurance includes VA (Veterans Administration),
  • some Railroad or Steelworkers health plans

TYPE of Services offered

  • Offers Nursing Care Services
  • Offers Physical Therapy Services
  • Offers Occupational Therapy Services
  • Offers Speech Pathology Services
  • Offers Medical Social Services
  • Offers Home Health Aide Services
